<p>Use <code>.ratio-[width]x[height]</code> utility classes to control
the aspect ratio of an element. These classes apply the
<code>aspect-ratio</code> CSS property to enforce consistent
width-to-height proportions.</p>
<h3 id="doc-syntax">Syntax</h3>
<pre class="html"><code>.ratio-[width]x[height]</code></pre>
<p>This sets:</p>
<pre class="css"><code>aspect-ratio: [width] / [height] !important;</code></pre>
<h3 id="doc-examples">Examples</h3>
<div class="mt-4 w-128px ratio-1x1 bg-blue border rounded text-center">
1:1
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;mt-4 w-128px ratio-1x1 bg-blue border rounded&quot;&gt;1:1&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
<div class="mt-4 w-128px ratio-16x9 bg-blue border rounded text-center">
16:9
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;mt-4 w-128px ratio-16x9 bg-blue border rounded&quot;&gt;16:9&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
